The paper deals with game theory and algorithmic complexity, which are both central topics in computer science. The focus on imperfect recall games and the search for efficient algorithms to find solution concepts suggest that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of computational complexity theory to analyze the difficulty of finding solution concepts also suggests that the paper could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
